Inspect Element in mobile phone

Method 2: Inspect Element Bookmarklet (No Computer Required)
You can inject a lightweight inspector (like Eruda) directly into any mobile page using a bookmark. 
Create a new bookmark in Chrome mobile.
Edit the bookmark and change the name to "Inspect Element".
Paste the following code into the URL field:
javascript:(function () { var script = document.createElement('script'); script.src='//cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/eruda'; document.body.appendChild(script); script.onload = function () { eruda.init() } })();
To use it: Visit any website, tap the address bar, type "Inspect Element," and select the bookmark you created. A gear icon will appear to open the inspector. 
